14:39.655 --> 14:40.979
He's sick as a dog.

14:41.354 --> 14:43.326
He told me he had to be
at the shoot at 7:00 a.m.

14:43.359 --> 14:45.221
Even turkeys aren't up at 7:00 a.m.

14:45.246 --> 14:47.463
What time are turkeys up, Mom?

14:47.496 --> 14:50.952
Don't you sass mouth me,
Timothy Dale Cramblin.

14:50.952 --> 14:52.034
I am here to pick up

14:52.068 --> 14:54.804
his Slipknot mask, his "Battlefield" disc

14:54.837 --> 14:56.706
and his "Five Nights at Freddy's" men.

14:56.739 --> 14:58.274
Yeah, well, you should take his sheet too,

14:58.307 --> 14:59.408
because it's caked.

14:59.442 --> 15:01.964
I'm sure I don't know what that means.

15:02.178 --> 15:03.301
Go get the stuff!

15:03.301 --> 15:05.176
Jerry wants to leave the
city before it's dark.

15:05.177 --> 15:06.449
He's terrified!

15:06.482 --> 15:07.693
All right, let's go, babe.

15:08.806 --> 15:10.734
Yo. How you doin'?

15:16.017 --> 15:18.261
He didn't even have the
balls to tell us to our face

15:18.294 --> 15:19.695
that he was gonna bail on us.

15:19.729 --> 15:21.122
You surprised?

15:21.122 --> 15:22.857
That's all he's ever done.

15:23.238 --> 15:26.101
How can you be so good at
this job and not wanna do it?

15:28.024 --> 15:29.079
What?

15:29.764 --> 15:30.879
Nothing.

15:31.216 --> 15:33.011
- Hey, Tim.
- Hey, Sam.

15:33.467 --> 15:35.169
♪ Mail's here ♪

15:35.202 --> 15:36.291
Boo-yah!

15:38.706 --> 15:40.541
What the hell is your
cousin David doing here?

15:40.574 --> 15:42.476
Oh, well, Tim, since I just found out

15:42.510 --> 15:45.079
about the open door policy
for hiring family members,

15:45.112 --> 15:47.715
I figured it'd be okay for
David to come work here.

15:48.147 --> 15:50.719
You're not mad, are you? You can't be.

15:50.751 --> 15:52.386
Yeah, all right. I get it.

15:52.420 --> 15:53.888
I'm sorry. It won't happen again.

15:53.921 --> 15:56.624
When you work at a company
where two people own it,

15:56.820 --> 15:59.293
all decisions need to go
through both of 'em, bud, okay?

15:59.326 --> 16:01.495
Yeah, you made your point, Sam.

16:01.529 --> 16:02.630
- Okay, that's all I'm sayin'.
- Okay.

16:02.663 --> 16:04.388
- All right? Okay?
- All right, cool.

16:04.413 --> 16:05.433
Great.

16:05.865 --> 16:06.901
Hey, David?

16:08.736 --> 16:10.438
All right, you can go on home.

16:10.776 --> 16:11.910
He got the point.

16:11.944 --> 16:14.178
- Got what?
- Tim got the prank.

16:15.080 --> 16:16.890
So this isn't a real job?

16:18.317 --> 16:19.279
Oh.

16:20.222 --> 16:21.617
Um, just one second.

16:23.801 --> 16:25.647
Joy. Hey.

16:26.306 --> 16:27.908
Yeah, the job's not real.

16:29.337 --> 16:30.825
Yeah, it was a prank on Tim.

16:32.778 --> 16:33.847
Okay.

16:34.179 --> 16:35.478
- Don't wave to us.
- Yeah.

16:35.478 --> 16:36.583
I'll do that. Sure.

16:37.847 --> 16:38.890
Guys...

16:41.391 --> 16:44.487
please, please, please don't do this!

16:44.520 --> 16:46.489
- I need this job.
- David, stand up.

16:46.522 --> 16:48.324
You can finish up the
rest of the week, okay?

16:48.358 --> 16:50.418
Thanks, Sam. I broke your stapler.

16:51.561 --> 16:53.896
Hey, David. What's... up?

16:54.779 --> 16:55.786
Just dumb.

16:56.083 --> 16:58.901
<i>We went the Pegasus.
I got a Wings jersey.</i>

16:59.584 --> 17:02.066
We even walked a block. Wasn't bad.

17:02.338 --> 17:04.140
That city's gotten okay.

17:04.743 --> 17:05.873
In certain parts.

17:06.179 --> 17:07.993
We were asked for change.

17:08.358 --> 17:10.760
But the guy was funny, actually.

17:12.636 --> 17:15.002
- Excuse me for a minute.
- Thank you.

17:15.672 --> 17:17.515
Chrissy and I applied and got in to be

17:17.515 --> 17:18.549
on "The New Dance Show."

17:18.582 --> 17:20.684
- Oh!
- Yeah, so excited.

17:26.577 --> 17:27.739
<i>Enter.</i>

17:30.127 --> 17:31.315
What the hell, man?

17:31.695 --> 17:33.364
You sneak back to Mom's
in the middle of the night,

17:33.397 --> 17:34.865
leave a puddle of rope on the bed?

17:35.404 --> 17:36.801
It's my two weeks notice.

17:36.834 --> 17:39.616
Trevor, you need to grow up.

17:40.004 --> 17:42.649
You can't just run away from everything.

17:43.514 --> 17:45.577
I'll tell you what. I'll give you a pass.

17:45.602 --> 17:46.950
You can come back and work for me.

17:46.975 --> 17:48.610
